==English==
===Noun===
'''teakettle''', ''less frequently'' '''tea kettle'''

# A vessel for boiling water for tea.
#: ''This lovely teakettle comes in three designer colors.''

===Usage note===
In British usage, '''the kettle''' is universally understood to mean a teakettle; one would usually say "Put the kettle on" and not "Put the teakettle on".

